dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset that contains 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for evaluating machine learning algorithms in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: J. Wu
Q. Zhang
G. Xu
dcterms:description: Tiny ImageNet is a subset of the ImageNet dataset, containing 100,000 images across 200 classes, with each class having 500 training images and 50 validation images. It is used for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: Tiny ImageNet
